items.title: Day 2 - a long coach trip from Zagreb to pick up our boat on the Adriatic coast at Neum. Once over the...

object.content:
Day 2 - a long coach trip from Zagreb to pick up our boat on the Adriatic coast at Neum. Once over the mountains from Zagreb and the sun comes out to play and stays almost to the end of our trip.

We had lunch by the wonderful viewpoint close to the new bridge over the Krka River looking towards Skradin and the opulent bay with it's yachts. A medieval town going back more than 1000 years...apparently Bill Gates visited the town in the Summer and named it his favourite vacation place in Forbes Magazine (ref. Wikipedia)....lunch was good by the way.

#Skradin #croatia ﻿

thumbnails.description: Close-up view of Skradin from the bridge restaurant area
Who's going to play Mum then Berta!
At last...our ship's cabin and home for the next 10 days or so
